About Curve DAO Token (CRV)

Curve Finance is a decentralized exchange (DEX) and automated market maker (AMM) protocol that was created in January 2020 by Michael Egorov. It is focused on stablecoin trading and yield optimization.
 In August 2020, Curve Finance launched Curve’s decentralized autonomous organization, called Curve DAO, as well as the CRV token. 
Curve DAO is governed by CRV token holders, who vote on issues including fees and liquidity pools. CRV token holders have voting rights within Curve DAO in order to give active participants in the protocol decision making power. CRV is an ERC-20 token that is compatible with the Ethereum ecosystem, as well as networks like Avalanche and Polygon via bridging. 
To participate in Curve DAO, you must lock up your CRV token(s) for a period of up to 4 years. You will then receive veCRV,  aka vote-escrowed CRV.  The longer you lock up your CRV for, the more veCRV you receive: 
1 CRV locked for 1 year = 0.25 veCRV 
1 CRV locked for 2 years = 0.50 veCRV 
1 CRV locked for 3 years = 0.75 veCRV 
1 CRV locked for 4 years = 1 veCRV 
CRV offers incentives for holding veCRV, such as: governance, larger share of platform fees, and up to 2.5x liquidity rewards. Owners of CRV are typically active DeFi traders and community-driven crypto enthusiasts.

Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging CRV from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap CRV from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.

  • What is a vote escrowed token?

    A vote escrowed token, aka a veToken—such as vCRV, is a type of token that is created by DeFi platforms. veTokens are typically used for governance on a platform, and for receiving rewards. Vote escrowed is a DeFi concept where you commit, or escrow, tokens for a set amount of time, and receive voting rights and benefits in return.

  • What can you do with Curve DAO Token?

    With Curve DAO Token, you can send and receive CRV, the network’s native token, and use it to pay transaction fees on certain networks. CRV is supported in decentralized apps for trading, staking, yield optimization, and payments. You can participate in DeFi protocols, bridge assets between networks, or use CRV in select web3 financial strategies, all with Ethereum-compatible speed and flexibility.

  • How do I trade Curve DAO Token for other cryptocurrencies?

    Trading Curve DAO Token (CRV) for ETH, WBTC, or SOL can be done directly in MetaMask. For more information on how to swap CRV, head to MetaMask Support.
